What you need to know:  A senior police officer was on Thursday evening stabbed to death while conducting a raid at an illicit brew den in Rumuruti, Laikipia County.Rumuruti Police Station Deputy Officer Commanding Police Station Prosper Wandera was stabbed by a chang'aa brewer and died on the spot during a raid at a chang'aa den at Maundu ni Meri in Laikipia West.The officer had reportedly gone to conduct a raid at the den in Sossian location within Maundu NiÂ Meri shopping centre when the 8 pm incident occurred, according to Laikipia County Police commander John Nyoike.